records.addlTxt:
Defendant Dustin E Flatow in court with attorney Jorge R Fragoso.  Timothy Suha appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant graduated from drug treatment court. State filed Amended Information. Court receives Amended Information.
Court lifts the stay and finds defendant of count 1 of the Amended Information. 
Count 1 amended to a misdemeanor possession charge, 961.41(3g)(d). Count 2 previously dismissed and read-in.

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

6 MONTHS JAIL (STRAIGHT TIME), w/Standard Release Conditions (CREDIT - 64 days if Revoked);

TERM OF PROBATION:  12 MONTHS - PROBATION MAY BE SERVED IN DANE COUNTY;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No operation of motor vehicle unless properly licenses.  

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 to be paid as a condition of probation;

Defendant to report to Probation by noon on May 24, 2016.

Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations.
